node.label: A new engagement follows the next 7 steps towards realisation. Through each step in the process data i generated and used in the next step.

To engage the consultants, Engagement Serach has to find projects. Both the company and the client search for eachother. When found, a realationship is started if the initial contact is satisfactory. Then projects and followup is done to prolong the relationship.

From the view of the company, the potential colleague has to pass the different constraints to receive a acontract from the company. The Business process works from the top down, where the numbered connectins are the important steps where both parties have to positively fit the constraint.
This is the view that binds the other views together. As the parent, it shows that all the children plays an important role to keep company growing.
Competence and experience increases towards the right and with the size of the contract(rectangle).
The yellow stairs represents the different levels of compensation. The more competent the employe, the better compensation.
The thirs stairs represent the mentality and the required skills at each level to be able to climb to the next level.
Stairs down right is the development of locations, incluence actors, over time.
Flow in the top right part show how locations are culturally linked by closeness.
Flow links in the bottom left shows how the company structure is mainly influenced, in business and strategic factors

The strategic values work from the inside out. Most important is the 'Why', followd by the 'How', and finally the 'What'. Within each category there are values that should be followed to acchieve greatness in the company.
- Solve Client challenges - Engage Client - Improve Client Business - Provide Value for Client - Enrich Knowledge Base
- Find Talent - Recruit Talent - Follow up Talent - Build Market understanding
- Find Clients - Client followup - Client Care - Build market understanding - Engage Consultants
The purpose of this networking model is to show which parts that does the networking activity. And to display how different parts depend on eachother.
The five activities ahve to be interact with actors that exectue other activities. Here the relationships between activities are modeled.
